Learn About Mott's
Flint Area Program









OUR GOALS
The Mott Foundation supports efforts that promote a just, equitable and sustainable society.
In each of our program areas — Civil Society, Education, Environment and Flint Area — we aim to inspire and empower individuals to work with their communities in ways that will help them achieve more than they could ever accomplish alone. 
See What We Do













Mott’s Response to the Flint Water Crisis

The Charles Stewart Mott Foundation has committed up to $100 million over five years to help our home community recover and rise from its water crisis. A new interactive feature reports on our grantmaking to date.




Explore the grants 

Pictured: Dr. Mona Hanna-Attisha and 4-year-old Hudson Walker. Dr. Hanna-Attisha directs the Pediatric Public Health Initiative, which seeks to mitigate, diagnose, treat and track health and behavioral impacts related to children’s lead exposure. It’s a collaboration between Michigan State University and Hurley Children’s Hospital. Photo by Douglas Pike, provided courtesy of Hurley Medical Center. 










